        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The tilt/telescoping steering column assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501201">Figure 1</hotlnk>) allows tilt and/or telescope functions through a common
                    lever.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0501201" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0501201" filename="../figg05/G0501201.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Tilt/Telescoping Steering Column Assembly</caption>
                </figure>
                <para>A steering wheel is connected to the steering column assembly. The steering column assembly is
                    connected to the steering shaft by a universal joint. The lower end of the steering shaft is
                    connected to the steering gear by a second universal joint. The universal joints permit correct
                    alignment and smooth rotation of the steering shaft to steering gear with no binding of the shafts.
                </para>
                <para>The turn signal assembly and trailer hand brake controls are mounted to the main housing
                    assembly.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
